LINK IN BIOüíôAfter my recent trip to Nepal I met @pembapatle (who is an incredible person and 8 time Everest summiteer!). He told me about the amazing work he is doing with Ascent Aid Nepal. Ascent Aid opened Shree Janata Basic school in 2018. Shree Janata Basic School is located in one of the most remote areas of the Himalayas at 2600 meters. 
In order to improve the school grounds, provide necessary school supplies for the children, and pay teachers salaries they need help. $150-$180 will pay a teachers salary for an entire month. The work Ascent Aid is doing is so important in helping establish better opportunities for the next generations of The Himalayas. If you wish to donate please visit the link in my bio, and read more about Ascent Aid at ascentaidnepal.org üíô
